Press room > Press releases > The new productive state-owned subsidiary company Pemex Logistics began operations









                                                                                                                
	
	
			The new productive state-owned subsidiary company Pemex Logistics began operations
		

                                                                                                                












                                                                                                                                                        Press releases
                                                                                                                                                        








Press releasesActualmente seleccionadoPresentations









Compartir
                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                            





















					15/10/2015
					| 90 
					


Contenido de la páginaGiven its size, it is one of the 5 major logistics companies in the world
The productive subsidiary company (SPC) Pemex Logistics today formally began its operations. During the first meeting of the Board of Directors of this company, the Board approved its organic statute, in compliance with the creation agreement published last October 1 in the Official Gazette of the Federation.
 
The General Director of the new SPC, Francisco Fuentes Saldaña, said that constitution of Pemex Logistics is of great importance because it integrates the activities of transportation, storage and distribution into one company including gas and refined products pipelines, storage and distribution terminals, as well as LPG, the maritime terminals and all maritime and ground transportation services.
 
He said that their main customers are currently Pemex Exploration and Production and Pemex Industrial Transformation and said the company has the capacity to give service to third parties.
 
As established in the Energy Reform, Pemex Logistics activities will be supervised by the Energy Regulatory Commission (CRE). Its objective will also be to participate in partnerships and alliances to strengthen the provision of transport and storage of hydrocarbons, oil and petrochemicals, in order to generate economic value.
 
This new EPS encompasses a network of 35,000 kilometers of pipelines and a storage capacity of over 50 million barrels of more than 30 products, which makes it one of the top five logistics companies in the world.
 
Fuentes Saldaña transmitted the commitment made by Pemex’s CEO and Chairman of the Board of Directors of Pemex Logistics, Emilio Lozoya, to renew the capacity to transform and have a new attitude of innovation to overcome the challenges of an open and competitive market.
 
The Board approves appointments
 
The Board of Directors of Pemex Logistics approved the appointment of the new Deputy Directors:
 
Luis Sanchez Graciano, Deputy Director of Transportation.  He is a Mechanical Engineer Electrician by the University of Guadalajara with expertise in business administration from the UNAM. He has worked for 28 years at Pemex, holding various positions. Acted to date as Deputy Director of Pemex Gas and Basic Petrochemicals Pipelines.
 
Luis Alberto Nuñez Santander, Deputy Director for Operations. Engineer in Electronics and Communications by UANL, and has worked for Pemex for 31 years, and acted as Head Coordinator of Operations at Pemex Refining.
 
Adrian Brígido Moral Piñeiro, Storage and Dispatch Deputy Director studied Engineering Management Systems from the Hispanic University. He has worked at Pemex for 33 years and served as Head of Distribution, Measurement & Services at Pemex Refining.
 
 










Las menciones de Pemex pueden referirse a Petróleos Mexicanos o a cualquiera de sus Empresas Productivas Subsidiarias.

