Industry News


                Energy            


5 things to know in Texas energy this week




Jul 25, 2017, 12:21pm CDT
















Joshua Mann


Reporter
Houston Business Journal









Joshua Mann


 


 







                    Share
                


























 Order Reprints


 Save Article




 Print





 










 



 Email




 Facebook




 LinkedIn




 Twitter




 Save Article





More 






 Email




 Facebook




 LinkedIn




 Twitter




 Save Article

















 














Joshua Mann


Reporter
Houston Business Journal





In This Article






Energy




Oil & gas





























Steve Kean




John Schmitz




Greg Goff




Dean Taylor






 


 















 Enlarge





                Steven J. Kean, president and CEO of Kinder Morgan Inc.            

                Photos by Craig Hartley/HBJ            






Deals took the spotlight in Texas energy news last week, which featured a merger, a Mexican logistical agreement and the overturning of a jury decision on a broken deal from 2014. Meanwhile, Kinder Morgan dropped some strong earnings numbers and Paragon came out of bankruptcy with a fresh board of directors. Here are five things to know in Texas energy this week:
• Houston-based Kinder Morgan Inc. (NYSE: KMI) posted strong second-quarter earnings, saying it would increase its dividend by 60 percent for 2018 and 25 percent each year beyond that to 2020. It also managed to grow its backlog of projects to $12.2 billion, up $500 million from the first quarter. That growth can be funded through cashflow, without the need to seek additional debt, said Steve Kean, Kinder Morgan's CEO and president.











 Enlarge





                Steven J. Kean, president and CEO of Kinder Morgan Inc.            
Photos by Craig Hartley/HBJ






 


• Houston-based Rockwater Energy Solutions Inc. is planning an all-stock merger with Gainesville, Texas-based Select Energy Services Inc. (NYSE: WTTR). The combined company will operate under Select's name, and Select shareholders will own about 64.4 percent of the combined company. Holli Ladhani, currently the chairman, president and CEO of Rockwater, will be president and CEO of the combined company, while Select's top executive, John Schmitz, will be its executive chairman.




 


• San Antonio-based refining company Tesoro Corp. (NYSE: TSO) has come to an agreement with Pemex Logistics to use refined product pipelines and storage terminals owned by the state oil company in Baja California and Sonora, both in Mexico. "The expansion of our strategic footprint to include Northern Mexico strengthens our integrated value chain with significant growth opportunities for our marketing business," Tesoro CEO Greg Goff said in a statement. "We are excited about Mexico and the opportunity to create value for the company, customers, business partners and communities."
• Paragon Offshore Ltd., which has its principal executive offices in Houston, has come out of bankruptcy and is searching for a new CEO. Dean Taylor was named interim president and CEO in November, and the company's creditors have appointed a new board of directors, led by James Swent as the company's chairman. Swent is a director of Energy XXI Gulf Coast Inc. and the retired executive vice president and CFO of Ensco PLC.

• An appeals court in Dallas has overturned a landmark 2014 decision by a jury in a dispute between Houston-based Enterprise Products Partners LP (NYSE: EPD) and Dallas-based Energy Transfer Partners LP (NYSE: ETP). The jury originally found that Enterprise had wrongfully dropped Energy Transfer from a deal to build a pipeline from Cushing, Oklahoma, to the Gulf Coast, but a three-judge panel overturned that decision.







 





 















































 





















Kinder Morgan posts earnings; Select Energy, Rockwater to merge; Tesoro, Pemex reach logistics deal - Dallas Business Journal








































































 




























